---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Proportionality" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-7/" backLabel="← Grade 7">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Proportionality</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Recognize direct and inverse proportionality</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>When more really means more</h2>
		<p><strong>Direct proportionality:</strong> Twice as much gas → drive twice as far. The graph is a line through the origin.</p>
		<p><strong>Inverse proportionality:</strong> Twice as many workers → half the time. The graph is a hyperbola.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Seeing Proportionality</h3>
		<p>The line y = a·x always passes through (0,0). Change a — that's the proportionality constant!</p>
	</section>

	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fn={(x, a) => a * x} fnLabel="y = a·x" showSlider={true} sliderLabel="a" sliderMin={0.5} sliderMax={3} sliderStep={0.25} />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 How to Recognize</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Directly proportional:</strong> y/x = constant (quotient stays the same)</li>
			<li><strong>Inversely proportional:</strong> x·y = constant (product stays the same)</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
